ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Study ID number
Study condition to which participant was assigned
Notes: 1 = Cognitive remediation; 2 = Comparison condition; 3 = Other; 4= treatment as usual; 5= Computers first; 6= CRT first; 7=SCIT

ElementDescription: Assessment time point
Notes: 1=Baseline (STARD); 2=Level exit (STARD); 3= Quarterly follow up (STARD);5= Screening; 10= Baseline; 21, 22, 23 = Mid-point 1, 2, 3; 30= End-of-treatment; 41, 42, 43= Follow-up1, 2, 3 etc.; 601 = 6 Month Reassessment ; 602 = 12 Month Reassessment ; 603 = 18 Month Reassessment; 604 = 5 mins before infusion; 605 = 40 mins after infusion; 606 = 100 mins after infusion; 607 = the 5th or 15th visit

ElementDescription: Days since baseline
Dual span length (i.e. lowest level -1 at which 2/3 number sequences are recalled incorrectly) minus one
Dual task: percentage of sequences of span-1 length correct with span recall alone
Dual task: percentage of sequences of span-1 length correct at span recall with tracking
Dual task: percentage of incorrect sequences in span recall with tracking where all no.s were correct but  misordered
percent of incorrect sequences in span recall with tracking where extra no.s were added to an otherwise correct sequence
percent of incorrect sequences in which a single number is omitted from an otherwise correct sequence
percent of sequences which were incorrect due to other errors (i.e. those not included in other error variables)
Dual task: tracking speed level
Dual task: Percentage of time on target in first minute - tracking alone
Dual task: Percentage of time on target in second minute - tracking alone
Dual task: Percentage time on target in third minute - tracking alone
Dual task: average percentage time on target over minutes 1, 2 and 3 - tracking alone
Dual task: percentage time on target in first 30 seconds - tracking with span recall
Dual task: percentage time on target in 2nd 30 seconds - tracking with span recall
Dual task: percentage time on target in 3rd 30 seconds - tracking with span recall
Dual task: percentage time on target in 4th 30 seconds - tracking with span recall
Dual task: percentage time on target in 5th 30 seconds - tracking with span recall
Dual task: percentage time on target in 6th 30 seonds - tracking with span recall
Dual task: average of trspa1 and trspa2 (for use in observing practice effects)
Dual task: average of trsap3 and trspa4 (practice effects)
Dual task: average of trspa5 and trspa6 (practice effects)
Dual task: overall mean of percentage time on target in 6 30 second episodes of tracking with span recall
